HimPEN.name: HimPEN
HimPEN.description: Octet String for storing PEN numbers. The format is The PEN is displayed in the following format: [LTG]-[LTU]-[EBT]. LTG: Line/Trunk Group: always 1 LTU: Line/Trunk Unit: a number between 1 and 99 EBT: a three-digit number.

HimPabxId.name: HimPabxId
HimPabxId.description: Textual convention for the Pabx Id.

HimSwitchNumber.name: HimSwitchNumber
HimSwitchNumber.description: Data type of the switch number.

HimYesNo.name: HimYesNo
HimYesNo.description: Boolean data type: 1. no 2. yes The order is set like this to comply with the definition of data leaves in the hicom MIB that use this convention implicitly.

HimPhoneNumber.name: HimPhoneNumber
HimPhoneNumber.description: Convention that represents phone numbers in a HiPath system.

himWelPgSysNo.name: himWelPgSysNo
himWelPgSysNo.description: This field contains the system number (max. 17 characters).

himHP4KVersion.name: himHP4KVersion
himHP4KVersion.description: This field contains the Hicom/HiPath version number of the system (max. 4 characters).

himSystemRelease.name: himSystemRelease
himSystemRelease.description: This field contains the system release number of the system (max. 2 characters).

himRevisionLevel.name: himRevisionLevel
himRevisionLevel.description: This field contains the revision number of the system software (max. 2 characters).

himHWArchitecture.name: himHWArchitecture
himHWArchitecture.description: This field contains the information on hardware architecture in the format [hw-architecture][system-variant][hw-design] [hw-architecture] Abbreviation describing hardware architecture. F.i '4300', '350E', etc. [system-variant] H40: SYSTEM VARIANT 40 H80: SYSTEM VARIANT 80 H600: SYSTEM VARIANT 600 [hw-design] ECX: HARDWARE DESIGN EXTENDED COMPACT EXTENDED ECDSC: HARDWARE DESIGN EXTENDED COMPACT DSC CXE: HARDWARE DESIGN EXTENDED COMPACT CXE

himHWArchitectureType.name: himHWArchitectureType
himHWArchitectureType.description: This field contains abbreviation describing hardware architecture type (max. 3 characters).

himOperationMode.name: himOperationMode
himOperationMode.description: This field contains the operating mode of the system. Possible Values: SIMPLEX: OPERATING MODE SIMPLEX DUPLEX: OPERATING MODE DUPLEX REDUNDANCY

himSWUProc1.name: himSWUProc1
himSWUProc1.description: These fields contains the name of the SWU processor board (max. 8 characters). SWU = Switching Unit Possible values: - CC-A - CC-B

himSWUMemory1.name: himSWUMemory1
himSWUMemory1.description: These fields contain the size of the SWU memory for each processor card. SWU = Switching Unit

himSWUProc2.name: himSWUProc2
himSWUProc2.description: These fields contains the name of the SWU processor board (max. 8 characters). SWU = Switching Unit Possible values: - CC-A - CC-B

himSWUMemory2.name: himSWUMemory2
himSWUMemory2.description: These fields contain the size of the SWU memory for each processor card. SWU = Switching Unit

himTechInfoInfoNo.name: himTechInfoInfoNo
himTechInfoInfoNo.description: This field contains the number of the subsystem. This number can be assigned as required when configuring the subsystem.

himTechInfoDate.name: himTechInfoDate
himTechInfoDate.description: This field contains the date on which the subsystem was configured.

himTechInfoTechnicalData.name: himTechInfoTechnicalData
himTechInfoTechnicalData.description: This field contains the technical data of the subsystem.

himTechInfoNumber.name: himTechInfoNumber
himTechInfoNumber.description: This field contains the number of each subsystem configured.

himNotepadDataTable.name: himNotepadDataTable
himNotepadDataTable.description: This node contains the system data entered in a notepad. The table for notepad entries holds a maximum of 30 data records.

himNotepadDataInfoNo.name: himNotepadDataInfoNo
himNotepadDataInfoNo.description: This field contains the number of the subsystem. This number is assigned permanently when configuring the subsystem.

himNotepadDataDate.name: himNotepadDataDate
himNotepadDataDate.description: This field contains the date on which the subsystem was configured.

himNotepadDataText.name: himNotepadDataText
himNotepadDataText.description: This field contains the technical data of the subsystem.

himProjPlanInfoTable.name: himProjPlanInfoTable
himProjPlanInfoTable.description: This screen makes it possible to generate a file with project planning data.

himProjPlanInfoFile.name: himProjPlanInfoFile
himProjPlanInfoFile.description: This field contains the name of the project planning file.

himProjPlanInfoCreationDate.name: himProjPlanInfoCreationDate
himProjPlanInfoCreationDate.description: This field contains the date on which the project planning file was generated.

himProjPlanInfoCreationTime.name: himProjPlanInfoCreationTime
himProjPlanInfoCreationTime.description: This field contains the time at which the project planning file was generated.

himSpecShelfDataTable.name: himSpecShelfDataTable
himSpecShelfDataTable.description: All subscriber and trunk-related lines are grouped within LTU (Line/Trunk Unit) frames. Each frame has several slots for modules. The frame is connected to the system via the LTUC control board. This table contains the frame configuration.

himSpecShelfDataAddress.name: himSpecShelfDataAddress
himSpecShelfDataAddress.description: This field contains the address of the shelf in format LTG.LTU. LTG:Line/Trunk Group LTU: Line/Trunk Unit

himSpecShelfDataFrameType.name: himSpecShelfDataFrameType
himSpecShelfDataFrameType.description: This field contains the part number of the frame.

himSpecShelfDataLTU.name: himSpecShelfDataLTU
himSpecShelfDataLTU.description: This field contains type of LTU (Line/Trunk Unit) frame. Possible values for LTU frame type: - PREATL - frametype for Preatlantic Hicom Types - CC40F - basisframe for 40CMX - CC80W - basisframe for 80CMX - CC80F - basisframe for 80CMX/DSC and CXE - L80XF - for 80CMX/DSC, CXE, 600ECS and AP shelves - L80XW - extension frame for 80CMX/DSC - LTUW - frame for 600ECX and AP shelves Possible values for AP shelf type: - L80XF - for 80CMX/DSC, CXE, 600ECS and AP shelves - LTUW - frame for 600ECX and AP shelves - INCH19 - 19 inch frame for AP shelves

himSpecShelfDataNetworkType.name: himSpecShelfDataNetworkType
himSpecShelfDataNetworkType.description: This field contains connection type of LTU frame / AP shelf.

himSpecShelfDataNetworkAddress.name: himSpecShelfDataNetworkAddress
himSpecShelfDataNetworkAddress.description: This field contains network IP address.

himSpecShelfDataRemote.name: himSpecShelfDataRemote
himSpecShelfDataRemote.description: This field shows if frame is remote. Possible values: - yes - frame is remote - no - frame is not remote

himSpecShelfDataLocation.name: himSpecShelfDataLocation
himSpecShelfDataLocation.description: This field contains postal address (city, street, building, ..) , where a FLEX LTU or an AP shelf is located.

himSpecShelfDataLTUC.name: himSpecShelfDataLTUC
himSpecShelfDataLTUC.description: This field contains part number adding LTUC module. LTUC: Line/Trunk Unit Control.

himSWUBoardTable.name: himSWUBoardTable
himSWUBoardTable.description: This table contains the configuration of the peripheral boards. Periphery Assemblies Peripheral and ring generator assemblies as well as SIU are configured in the LTU. The board is entered in the SWU database. LTU = Line/Trunk Unit SIU = Signaling Interface Unit SWU = Switching Unit

himSWUBoardPEN.name: himSWUBoardPEN
himSWUBoardPEN.description: This field contains the name of the board PEN. PEN: Port Equipment Number The PEN is displayed in the following format: [LTG]-[LTU]-[EBT]. LTG: Line/Trunk Group LTU: Line/Trunk Unit EBT: Slot

himSWUBoardOverlayLTU.name: himSWUBoardOverlayLTU
himSWUBoardOverlayLTU.description: This field contains the name of the overlay LTU (Line/Trunk Unit).

himSWUBoardType.name: himSWUBoardType
himSWUBoardType.description: This field contains the name of the configured board.

himSWUBoardNominal.name: himSWUBoardNominal
himSWUBoardNominal.description: This field contains the name of the nominal board.

himSWUBoardActual.name: himSWUBoardActual
himSWUBoardActual.description: This field contains part number of the board that is plugged in.

hhimSWUBoardFirmware.name: hhimSWUBoardFirmware
hhimSWUBoardFirmware.description: This field contains the name of the firmware.

himSWUBoardRev.name: himSWUBoardRev
himSWUBoardRev.description: This field contains the revision of the board.

himSWUBoardFunctId.name: himSWUBoardFunctId
himSWUBoardFunctId.description: Function identification number for boards with more than one functions (e.g. SIUX, STMA, SLMO24).

himSWUBoardMode.name: himSWUBoardMode
himSWUBoardMode.description: This field contains the mode of the board. The mode is only displayed for the RG/ACGEN board.

himSWUBoardLWNo.name: himSWUBoardLWNo
himSWUBoardLWNo.description: This field contains the number of the loadware.

himSWUBoardLWInterVer.name: himSWUBoardLWInterVer
himSWUBoardLWInterVer.description: This field contains the interface version of the board.

himSWUBoardLWName.name: himSWUBoardLWName
himSWUBoardLWName.description: This field contains the file name of the loadware file or of the initialization file.

himSWUBoardLWDate.name: himSWUBoardLWDate
himSWUBoardLWDate.description: This field contains the date on which the loadware or the initialization file was generated.

himPSIOAssTable.name: himPSIOAssTable
himPSIOAssTable.description: This table contains the PSIO assemblies data.

himPSIOAssAssembly.name: himPSIOAssAssembly
himPSIOAssAssembly.description: This field contains the name of the PSIO board. PSIO: Peripheral Serial Input Output

himPSIOAssPEN.name: himPSIOAssPEN
himPSIOAssPEN.description: This field contains the name of the board PEN. PEN: Port Equipment Number The PEN is displayed in the following format: [LTG]-[LTU]-[EBT]. LTG: Line/Trunk Group LTU: Line/Trunk Unit EBT: Slot

himPSIOAssActual.name: himPSIOAssActual
himPSIOAssActual.description: This field contains the part number of the PSIO board.

himPSIOAssFirmware.name: himPSIOAssFirmware
himPSIOAssFirmware.description: This field contains the firmware name of the PSIO board.

himSerialLineTable.name: himSerialLineTable
himSerialLineTable.description: This table contains the serial interfaces data.

himSerialLineBoardType.name: himSerialLineBoardType
himSerialLineBoardType.description: This field contains abbreviation name of the board type.

himSerialLineNumber.name: himSerialLineNumber
himSerialLineNumber.description: This field contains the physical line number of the interface. Possible Values: numeric, 8-63

himSerialLineSpeed.name: himSerialLineSpeed
himSerialLineSpeed.description: This field contains standardized transmission speed (baud rate). Possible Values: 50, 100, 200, 300, 600, 1200, 2400, 4800, 9600, 19200.

himSerialLineLogDevName.name: himSerialLineLogDevName
himSerialLineLogDevName.description: This field contains the logical device name of the line. Possible Values: Value - Description CON1 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION,TERMINAL 1 CON2 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION,TERMINAL 2 CON3 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION,TERMINAL 3 CON4 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION,TERMINAL 4 CON5 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION 5 CON6 - LOGICAL DEVICE CONNECTION 6 PR1 - LOGICAL DEVICE:LINE PRINTER 1 PR2 - LOGICAL DEVICE:LINE PRINTER 2 PR3 - LOGICAL DEVICE:LINE PRINTER 3 PR4 - LOGICAL DEVICE:LINE PRINTER 4

himSerialLineDevType.name: himSerialLineDevType
himSerialLineDevType.description: This field contains the device type of the line. Possible Values: Value - Description PT88 - DEVICE TYPE QUOSC - QUME-ONLY-SCREEN QUOPT - QUME-ONLY-PT88 QUSCAPT - QUME-SCREEN-AND-PT88 PCOSC - PC-D-ONLY-SCREEN PCOPT - PC-D-ONLY-PT88 PCSCAPT - PC-D-SCREEN-AND-PT88 ASC - ASCII-CODE EBC - EBCDIC CODE RSV1 - RESERVED DEVICE TYPE 1 RSV2 - RESERVED DEVICE TYPE 2 RSV3 - RESERVED DEVICE TYPE 3

himSerialLineType.name: himSerialLineType
himSerialLineType.description: This field contains the line type (operation of synchronous lines (terminals) connected via V24 modems). Possible values: - ASY: asynchronous line type - V24: ccitt rec v24

himSCSIDevTable.name: himSCSIDevTable
himSCSIDevTable.description: This table contains the data for the SCSI devices connected.

himSCSIDevId.name: himSCSIDevId
himSCSIDevId.description: This field contains the type of SCSI device.

himSCSIDevType.name: himSCSIDevType
himSCSIDevType.description: This field contains the SCSI ID of the device.

himSCSIDevName.name: himSCSIDevName
himSCSIDevName.description: This field contains the name of the SCSI device in format: [vendor] [product number].

himSCSIDevFirmware.name: himSCSIDevFirmware
himSCSIDevFirmware.description: This field contains the firmware name of the SCSI device.

himSCSIDevLoadDrive.name: himSCSIDevLoadDrive
himSCSIDevLoadDrive.description: This field displays (if activity is in progress) the device from which the operating system and the database are started.

himCabinetTable.name: himCabinetTable
himCabinetTable.description: This table contains the data for configuring the cabinets and frames in a system. They reflect the physical structure of the system.

himCabAddr.name: himCabAddr
himCabAddr.description: This field contains the cabinet address. Structure of cabinet address: P 1 01 | | |__Number of cabinet in cabinet row | |_____Units, position of cabinet row |_______Tens (P=0, Q=1), position of the cabinet

himCabCabinet.name: himCabCabinet
himCabCabinet.description: This field contains the name of the cabinet.

himCabPartNo.name: himCabPartNo
himCabPartNo.description: This field contains the part number of the cabinet.

himCabShelfNo.name: himCabShelfNo
himCabShelfNo.description: This field contains the number of the shelf.

himCabFrame.name: himCabFrame
himCabFrame.description: This field contains the name of the frame.

himCabPid1.name: himCabPid1
himCabPid1.description: This field contains the processor ID 1.

himCabPid2.name: himCabPid2
himCabPid2.description: This field contains the processor ID 2.

himCabPid3.name: himCabPid3
himCabPid3.description: This field contains the processor ID 2.

himCabLTUNo.name: himCabLTUNo
himCabLTUNo.description: This field contains the number of the LTU (Line/Trunk Unit). The LTU range is divided in two parts: HHS (HICOM Host System) and AP (Access Point). The available values of the ranges are: HHS 1-15 and AP 17-99. The LTU 16 is forbidden. There are existing shelfes which are allowed only in HHS and others which are allowed only in the AP range.

himMemScalingTable.name: himMemScalingTable
himMemScalingTable.description: This screen contains the memory parameters for each of the devices or features specified. The values are only displayed in Configuration Management. See also DIMSU parameter list.

himMemScalingUnit.name: himMemScalingUnit
himMemScalingUnit.description: This field contains the parameter name (AMO DIMSU).

himMemScalingUsed.name: himMemScalingUsed
himMemScalingUsed.description: This value specifies the number of memory elements already used up. The comparison with the value in the Maximum field indicates how much of the allocated memory is still available for configuring devices or features.

himMemScalingMaxUsed.name: himMemScalingMaxUsed
himMemScalingMaxUsed.description: This field contains the number of memory elements allocated.

himMemScalingAllocated.name: himMemScalingAllocated
himMemScalingAllocated.description: This field displays the maximum number of memory elements that once have been used up during the lifetime of the switch ('high water mark'). It gives an indication how much memory was necessary at one time, so it is advised to not reduce the Maximum value below this value.

himMemScalingStandard.name: himMemScalingStandard
himMemScalingStandard.description: Standard is the advised value to be set in the Maximum field, if you don't have special needs to set it to a specific value. If you set all devices and features to the standard values it is guaranteed that you don't run out of DIMSU memory.

himMemScalingSysMax.name: himMemScalingSysMax
himMemScalingSysMax.description: This field contains the maximum number of possible memory elements.

himDBConfSysClass1.name: himDBConfSysClass1
himDBConfSysClass1.description: This field contains the name of the system.

himDBConfSysClass2.name: himDBConfSysClass2
himDBConfSysClass2.description: This field contains the coded name of the system.

himDBConfSysHWAss1.name: himDBConfSysHWAss1
himDBConfSysHWAss1.description: This field contains the hardware ID of the system.

himDBConfSysHWAss2.name: himDBConfSysHWAss2
himDBConfSysHWAss2.description: This field contains the shortened hardware ID of the system.

himDBConfSysDevLine1.name: himDBConfSysDevLine1
himDBConfSysDevLine1.description: This field contains the name of the product line.

himDBConfSysDevLine2.name: himDBConfSysDevLine2
himDBConfSysDevLine2.description: This field contains the shortened name of the product line. Possible values: - H300: EUROPE DEVELOPMENT - HUSA: US DEVELOPMENT

himDBConfSysOpMode.name: himDBConfSysOpMode
himDBConfSysOpMode.description: This field contains the operating mode of the system. Possible Values: - SIMPLEX: OPERATING MODE SIMPLEX - DUPLEX: OPERATING MODE DUPLEX REDUNDANCY

himDBConfSysResType.name: himDBConfSysResType
himDBConfSysResType.description: This field contains the restart identifier.

himDBConfSysHWArch.name: himDBConfSysHWArch
himDBConfSysHWArch.description: This field contains the name of the hardware architecture.

himDBConfSysHWArchType.name: himDBConfSysHWArchType
himDBConfSysHWArchType.description: This field contains the name of the hardware architecture type.

himDBConfSysNo.name: himDBConfSysNo
himDBConfSysNo.description: This field contains the number of the system.

himDBConfSysLoc.name: himDBConfSysLoc
himDBConfSysLoc.description: This field contains the name of the location in which the system is installed. Possible Values: - CUSTOMER (customer) - SUPPORT (support) - TESTLAB (testlab)

himDBConfSysBaseApp.name: himDBConfSysBaseApp
himDBConfSysBaseApp.description: This field contains the name of the base application.

himDBConfSysDBApp.name: himDBConfSysDBApp
himDBConfSysDBApp.description: This field contains the name of the database application.

himDBConfSysID.name: himDBConfSysID
himDBConfSysID.description: This field contains the system identification.

himDBConfHWLTG.name: himDBConfHWLTG
himDBConfHWLTG.description: This field contains the number of LTGs in the system. LTG: Line/Trunk Group

himDBConfHWLTU.name: himDBConfHWLTU
himDBConfHWLTU.description: This field contains the number of LTUs in the system. LTU: Line/Trunk Unit

himDBConfHWLines.name: himDBConfHWLines
himDBConfHWLines.description: This field contains the number of lines in the system.

himDBConfHWPorts.name: himDBConfHWPorts
himDBConfHWPorts.description: This field contains the number of ports in the system.

himDBConfHWPBC.name: himDBConfHWPBC
himDBConfHWPBC.description: This field contains the number of peripheral board controllers (PBC) in the system.

himDBConfHWMTSBdPerGSN.name: himDBConfHWMTSBdPerGSN
himDBConfHWMTSBdPerGSN.description: This field contains the number of memory time switches (MTS) per group switching network (GSN).

himDBConfHWSIUPPerLTU.name: himDBConfHWSIUPPerLTU
himDBConfHWSIUPPerLTU.description: This field contains the number of SIUP boards per LTU (Line/Trunk Unit).

himDBConfHWDIUCPerLTU.name: himDBConfHWDIUCPerLTU
himDBConfHWDIUCPerLTU.description: This field contains the number of DIUC boards per LTU (Line/Trunk Unit).

himDBConfHWHwyPerMTSBd.name: himDBConfHWHwyPerMTSBd
himDBConfHWHwyPerMTSBd.description: This field contains the number highways (HYW) per MTS board.

himDBConfHWHDLCPerDCL.name: himDBConfHWHDLCPerDCL
himDBConfHWHDLCPerDCL.description: This field contains the number of high level data link control (HDLC) channels per data communication link (DCL).

himDBConfHWPBCPerDCL.name: himDBConfHWPBCPerDCL
himDBConfHWPBCPerDCL.description: This field contains the number of peripheral board controllers (PBC) per data communication link (DCL).

himDBConfHWStdSIULine.name: himDBConfHWStdSIULine
himDBConfHWStdSIULine.description: This field contains the number of signaling unit lines. SIU: Signaling-Unit

himDBConfHWConfLine.name: himDBConfHWConfLine
himDBConfHWConfLine.description: This field contains the number of lines in the CONFERENCE board.

himDBConfHWDBDim.name: himDBConfHWDBDim
himDBConfHWDBDim.description: This field contains the name of the database dimensioning.

himDBConfHWTableVer.name: himDBConfHWTableVer
himDBConfHWTableVer.description: This field contains the version of the Conf table.

himHWArch.name: himHWArch
himHWArch.description: This field contains the name of the hardware architecture.

himHWArchType.name: himHWArchType
himHWArchType.description: This field contains the name of the hardware architecture type.

himHWOpMode.name: himHWOpMode
himHWOpMode.reference: Should be the same as himDBConfSysOpMode.
himHWOpMode.description: This field contains the name of the operating mode.

himHWSWUProc1.name: himHWSWUProc1
himHWSWUProc1.description: These fields contain the name of the SWU processor board (max. 8 characters). SWU = Switching Unit Possible values: - CC-A - CC-B

himHWSWUMem1.name: himHWSWUMem1
himHWSWUMem1.description: These fields contain the size of the SWU memory for each processor board. SWU = Switching Unit

himHWSWUProc2.name: himHWSWUProc2
himHWSWUProc2.description: These fields contain the name of the SWU processor board (max. 8 characters). SWU = Switching Unit Possible values: - CC-A - CC-B

himHWSWUMem2.name: himHWSWUMem2
himHWSWUMem2.description: These fields contain the size of the SWU memory for each processor board. SWU = Switching Unit

himHWADPProc.name: himHWADPProc
himHWADPProc.description: This field contains the name of the ADP processor.

himHWADPMem.name: himHWADPMem
himHWADPMem.description: This field contains the size of memory used by the ADP.

himLWOnCBAss.name: himLWOnCBAss
himLWOnCBAss.description: This field contains the hardware ID of the board. Note: Certain types of processor boards (e. g. DPC5) are using only firmware. Therefore, no loadware data is displayed and this field remains empty.

himLWOnCBPBCAddr.name: himLWOnCBPBCAddr
himLWOnCBPBCAddr.description: This field contains the peripheral board controller (PBC) address of the module. Note: Certain types of processor boards (e. g. DPC5) are using only firmware. Therefore, no loadware data is displayed and this field remains empty.

himLWOnCBFileName.name: himLWOnCBFileName
himLWOnCBFileName.description: This field contains the filename of the loadware file. Note: Certain types of processor boards (e. g. DPC5) are using only firmware. Therefore, no loadware data is displayed and this field remains empty.

himLWOnCBProdTime.name: himLWOnCBProdTime
himLWOnCBProdTime.description: This field contains the production date of the loadware. Note:Certain types of processor boards (e. g. DPC5) are using only firmware. Therefore, no loadware data is displayed and this field remains empty.

himLWOnProcAss.name: himLWOnProcAss
himLWOnProcAss.description: This field contains the name of the directory where the file with information on Loadware resides, e. g. CCA, CCB or ADP (max. 3 characters).

himLWOnProcInfoType.name: himLWOnProcInfoType
himLWOnProcInfoType.description: This field contains the boot type. It represents the file name also.

himLWOnProcLWId.name: himLWOnProcLWId
himLWOnProcLWId.description: This field contains the name of the loadware.

himLWOnProcLWIdCMP.name: himLWOnProcLWIdCMP
himLWOnProcLWIdCMP.description: This field contains the name of the loadware ID for the CMP. This field contains the '-' character if it is not relevant to this board.

himLWOnProcLWIdLP.name: himLWOnProcLWIdLP
himLWOnProcLWIdLP.description: This field contains the name of the loadware ID for the LP. This field contains the '-' character if it is not relevant to this board.

himLWOnCSIUTable.name: himLWOnCSIUTable
himLWOnCSIUTable.description: This table contains the loadware data on the central SIU (Signaling Interface Unit).

himLWOnCSIUNominal.name: himLWOnCSIUNominal
himLWOnCSIUNominal.description: This field contains the name of the nominal SIU (Signaling Interface Unit).

himLWOnCSIULWNo.name: himLWOnCSIULWNo
himLWOnCSIULWNo.description: This field contains the name of the SIU (Signaling Interface Unit) loadware.

himLWOnCSIUProc.name: himLWOnCSIUProc
himLWOnCSIUProc.description: This field contains the name of the processor in the SIU (Signaling Interface Unit).

himLWOnCSIUSlot.name: himLWOnCSIUSlot
himLWOnCSIUSlot.description: This field contains the name of the SIU (Signaling Interface Unit) slot.

himLWOnCSIUActual.name: himLWOnCSIUActual
himLWOnCSIUActual.description: This field contains the name of the current SIU (Signaling Interface Unit).

himLWOnCSIUFileName.name: himLWOnCSIUFileName
himLWOnCSIUFileName.description: This field contains the file name of the loadware file or of the initialization file.

himLWOnCSIUFileProd.name: himLWOnCSIUFileProd
himLWOnCSIUFileProd.description: This field contains the date on which the loadware or the initialization file was generated.

himMacAddrTable.name: himMacAddrTable
himMacAddrTable.description: This table contains the C-LAN and IPDA MAC addresses which are read during the boot process.

himMacAddrProc.name: himMacAddrProc
himMacAddrProc.description: This field contains the name of the processor (CCA, CCB or ADP - max 3 characters). It is also the name of the Unix directory where the file with information on MAC address resides.

himMacAddrInfoType.name: himMacAddrInfoType
himMacAddrInfoType.description: This field contains the condition on which the mac addresses are available.

himMacAddrCLan.name: himMacAddrCLan
himMacAddrCLan.description: This field contains the MAC address for UW7 part. The format is following: 'xx xx xx xx xx xx'.

himMacAddrIPDA.name: himMacAddrIPDA
himMacAddrIPDA.description: This field contains the MAC address for RMX part. The format is following: 'xx xx xx xx xx xx'.

himMarkFeatVer.name: himMarkFeatVer
himMarkFeatVer.description: This field contains the version of the software package. Format explanation: H 2 04 | |__SW version (01=EV1.0; 02=EV2.0; 03=EV3.0; 04=HiPath 4000 V1.0; 05=HiPath 4000 V2.0; 06=HiPath 4000 V3.0) | |_____Marketing concept (1=Old, 2=New)

himMarkFeatSerNo.name: himMarkFeatSerNo
himMarkFeatSerNo.description: This field contains the serial number of the software package.

himMarkFeatHWId.name: himMarkFeatHWId
himMarkFeatHWId.description: This field contains the dongle ID of the hardware dongle connected.

himMarkFeatInstallDate.name: himMarkFeatInstallDate
himMarkFeatInstallDate.description: This field contains the date on which the code word was entered.

himMarkFeatExpiryDate.name: himMarkFeatExpiryDate
himMarkFeatExpiryDate.description: This field contains the date on which the code word will expire.

himMarkFeatConfCode.name: himMarkFeatConfCode
himMarkFeatConfCode.description: This field contains codeword entry confirmation code.

himMarkFeatTrialModeAct.name: himMarkFeatTrialModeAct
himMarkFeatTrialModeAct.description: This field shows whether trial mode is active. Possible values: - yes - trial mode is activated - no - trial mode is not activated

himMarkFeatTrialRemDays.name: himMarkFeatTrialRemDays
himMarkFeatTrialRemDays.description: This field contains number of remaining days of an active trial mode.

himSalesFeatMarketPackId.name: himSalesFeatMarketPackId
himSalesFeatMarketPackId.description: This column contains the CM ids of the marketing packages.

himSalesFeatMarketPack.name: himSalesFeatMarketPack

himSysBasicNodeNo.name: himSysBasicNodeNo
himSysBasicNodeNo.description: HiPath node number. This field contains the globally unique number of your own PABX. This has a hierarchical structure containing different levels in Version V1.0 and later. Up to three values of the format: L2- L1- L0 can be used for numbering a system. - L2: area number in level 2 - L1: area number in level 1 - L0: area number in level 0 or node number in the old sense. If the value '0' is selected for a level, this means that the relevant hierarchical level is not being used for node numbering: '0' is equal to 'nothing' or 'level is not set'. With the help of this new node number format it is now possible to implement node numbers in networks in which - just as with dial numbers - the network hierarchy is reflected in the node numbers. The same numbering level (= number of levels set in the node number) must be used for all nodes in a network. This field will always show a three-level display with leading zeroes for levels not used for systems in Version V1.0 and later. Example: - 0-0-100 for 1-level numbering - 0-1-101 for 2-level numbering - 1-2-300 for 3-level numbering Values: 0-9 and '-' with format 22-111-000 Level 0 (000) 0-999 Level 1 (111) 0-253 Level 2 (22) 0-29 Max. 10 digits

himSysBasicLEGK.name: himSysBasicLEGK
himSysBasicLEGK.description: This field tells if the 'LEGK' feature is activated on the system. LEGK is a process within the call processing of HiPath 4000 with the following functions: - Gate keeper function: IP address resolution mechanism for IP trunking requiring the HG3550 board as hardware. - Resource Management: This function monitors network component usage for controlling IP trunking, IPDA scenarios, HFA and direct media connections. The LEGK can be activated at every HiPath 4000 in the network. Alternatively, it can be configured on a specific HiPath 4000 system only.
